Detailed Description

An annotated NSMutableData type.

CPNumericData combines a mutable data buffer with information about the data (shape, data type, size, etc.). The data is assumed to be an array of one or more dimensions of a single type of numeric data. Each numeric value in the array, which can be more than one byte in size, is referred to as a "sample". The structure of this object is similar to the NumPy ndarray object.

Property Documentation

- CPMutableNumericData: [read, write, copy]

The shape of the data buffer array.

The shape describes the dimensions of the sample array stored in the data buffer. Each entry in the shape array represents the size of the corresponding array dimension and should be an unsigned integer encoded in an instance of NSNumber.
